Think the Warawara that became me got all gnawed up by Willem DaPelican

Huh... Hm.. We spend the whole movie following a white man in Johannesburg as he ever slowly finds it in his heart to care about the well-being of these aliens (even though they somehow understand each other’s language at a level of fluency from the get go?) yet the only real peace solution in the end is for the aliens to go back to where they came from. This very half baked allusion to apartheid is made worse by the…

Diminishing returns. Starts with some of the finest practical body horror I’ve seen and by the end it felt like the prop department was looting a party city.. made me realize the importance of a believable and consistent world build in the horror genre, otherwise it’s like having a nightmare but then you have dildo hands and things are just silly.
Keep such atrocious visions between your head and the pillow, mister Tippett.
It’s good to give masterpieces 5 stars, no?

The criticisms I’m reading seem so nitpicky to me. I think Greta did exactly what she needed to do in order to make a movie that the masses could digest. Is it flawlessly nuanced and intentioned? No, but she cannonballed into uncharted waters as far as where I thought a blockbuster movie could go and she took the girls grandmas and gays with her (and from my intel, even the bros have been showing out and enjoying!) To do that and still make a movie that felt so uncompromisingly her — just say thanks guys!

It sucks being a descendent of an atrophied mafia family because all the special accommodations, drugs and money are gone but the emotional whiplash and general means of relating to other people is still this to a tee :/

This movie is so generous I was straight up blushing at how many thoughtful, intricate choices were made during the creation of it. All for us?!? The little ants that came together to watch lights go blinky on the big screen?! I have never heard an audience more gleefully applaud after a movie and I was a giddy participant in that hand chatter. (P.S. [partial spoiler] Jake kept feeding me edibles during this which I could not resist obviously and…
